description:
The official comic book of the most popular web series right now!

Follow the adventures of Arthéon the warrior, chief of the disastrous Noob guild, Gaea the summoner, Omega Zell the macho and egocentric assassin, without forgetting the worst one of all: Bandaid the simpleton priest. They will have to stand each other to explore dungeons, cross vast planes, and confront terrible monsters to get from level to level.

description:
A NEW CYCLE BEGINS !

Ten years have passed since the war, Link-Arkhoïde is in peace. The Okrane became a young Republic. And the Zeïd, always austere, is now headed by politik's children. Yet the Rhoukes clans once fearful nomads, led by an obscure goddess, attack Zeïd without any reason, ravaging everything.And nobody knows if Slhoka still has the Power?

New arc in 3 volumes.

description:
Imprisoned in Jaïpurna, will Slhoka manage to find himself?

Slhoka, who has become the guardian of power, remains stuck in Jaïpurna after his final battle against the goddess Ishtor.

Shanî took advantage of his splitting into two to steal his body and thus become his own master and create his own empire.In order to find himself, he has to deal with the one and the others without them killing each other because, without them, he cannot act, and even worse: he is at the mercy of just anyone...
name: L'Épingle des éphémères

description:
100-page special edition!

Wolverine's healing factor is gone for good, and his enemies know it! The sinister Mystique invades the Jean Grey School and Batroc the Leaper attacks! More action from Paul Cornell and Alan Davis!

A new saga begins: 'The Good, the Bad and the Ugly'! Deadpool discovers the truth behind his origin, and enlists the aid of Wolverine and Captain America! By Brian Posehn, Gerry Duggan and Declan Shalvey!

Featuring material first printed in Wolverine #9-10 and Deadpool #15-17.

description:
76 Action-Packed Pages in the Mighty Marvel Manner!

Arnim Zola may be dead, but can Captain America stop his battle station and army of mutates from invading the Earth?!

Also: Iron Man and Death's Head are going after the renegade robot 451!

Plus: Three Thors versus one God Butcher! ‘Nuff Said!

By Rick Remender, John Romita Jr, Kieron Gillen, Greg Land, Jason Aaron and Esad Ribic!

Includes material reprinted from Captain America Vol.7 #10, Iron Man Vol.6 #9 and Thor: God of Thunder #9!

description:
Gina Diggers and her adopted sister Britanny "Cheetah" Diggers search for an ancient time machine within a cave in the British countryside, which turns out to be the hidden lair of the Iron dragon Dreadwing and his slaves, the elves Tark and Mesha. The sisters must decide whom to help and what to do with the broken time machine, the Time Raft.

This issue is the 1994 black&white collected reprinting of the very first Gold Digger 4-issue storyarc first published in Mangazine Vol.2 #11-14. It includes 3 single-page pin-ups of Cheetah at the end.

description: Cover story is a German translation of Action Comics #484 - Superman Takes a Wife!

Fred Perry's super-scientist/archaeologist Gina Diggers and Ben Dunn's time-traveling high school teacher Mita Celande team up with their friends and family to stop the time-traveling, super-intelligent, evil dog Dr. Peachbody from erasing them from history in his attempt to ensure the realization of his alternate future where mankind are dogs' best slaves.

Trade paperback collecting the 8 black&white issues encompassing the Gold Digger / Ninja High School crossover Timewarp storyarc. It includes Gold Digger #32-35 and Ninja High School #54-57.

description: The complete guide to the world of Gold Digger! A great reference guide for new readers and a definite must-have for long-time fans. Volume 1 contains detailed synopses and artist commentaries for the Managazine Special (covering the very first story arc in Mangazine #11-14), the original black-and-white 4-issue Gold Digger mini-series, issues 1-25 of the black-and-white series, and some specials and crossovers. Also included are some cameos from the issues, profile art, issue checklist, basic character profiles, basic guide to Gina's cars and tech, and maps for Jade, the Realm of the Undead, and the Diggers sisters' house! How can you say no?
